|---|---|
| Archived repo — remote push returns 403; fork blocked by GitHub | Absorption pattern: source code is locally cloned; absorbing repos have already landed the SOTA features. Stranded commit `a38a6fa` is documented here. Restore path: `gh repo restore KooshaPari/pheno-harness` (org-owner only). |
| dyn-rlvr cross-cutting | The nested RLVR runner in `eval/nested_rlvr.py` has no direct absorber within the eval-bench-qa ecosystem. The `TraceraSemanticPillar` adapter covers the scorer side; the RLVR runtime itself remains orphaned. Deferred to DAG-T3-006 (v3 scorecard). |
| HARBOR.md portage task schema duplication | `pheno-harness/HARBOR.md` and `portage/PRD.md` both define portage task schemas. The portage schema (GitTaskId with `git_url`/`git_commit_id`/`path`) is canonical; `pheno-harness/adapters/portage_adapter.py` reads it but does not duplicate it. Deemed ACCEPTABLE — adapter-bound schemas may reference but not clone upstream specs. |

